
1. Start Server
Run npm run dev to start server on port 5000 (default).

2. Test Endpoints (via Postman or Curl)
Register User
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/register

{
  "name": "Test Client",
  "email": "client@test.com",
  "password": "123"
}
Login User
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login

{
  "email": "client@test.com",
  "password": "123"
}
Returns Token

Create Service (Admin Only)
Need to manually set role='admin' in DB for first admin or adjust reg logic for testing. POST http://localhost:5000/api/services Headers: Authorization: Bearer <TOKEN>

{
  "name": "Full Body Massage",
  "description": "Relaxing massage",
  "price": 50,
  "duration": 60,
  "category": "spa"
}
Book Service
POST http://localhost:5000/api/bookings Headers: Authorization: Bearer <TOKEN>

{
  "serviceId": "<SERVICE_ID>"
}

